---
import LibraryStyleLayout from "../../astro/layouts/LibraryStyleLayout.astro";
import { base } from "astro:config/client";
---

<LibraryStyleLayout>
  <main class="responsive-container stt-navigation-main-content">
    <h1>Side Top Top Navigation</h1>
    <p>
      This component provides fully responsive navigation bars using css classes
      and attibutes
    </p>
    <h2>Base blocs:</h2>
    <p>
      To use the basic side-top-top navigation layout, you need the following
      structure:
    </p>
    <pre
      data-copyable-snippet><code>{`<header class="stt-component">
  <div class="stt-toolbar-container">
    <div class="stt-primary-topbar">
      <button data-stt-action="toggle" class="stt-button">
      </button>
      <div class="stt-primary-topbar-content">
        <h1 class="navbar-title">SamplePage</h1>
        <button class="search-area"></button
        >
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="stt-secondary-topbar">
    </div>
    <div class="stt-primary-sidebar" data-stt-element="sidebar">
      <div class="stt-primary-sidebar-top">  
        <button data-stt-action="dismiss" class="stt-button">
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="stt-overlay" data-stt-element="overlay"></div>
  </div>
</header>
<main class="responsive-container stt-navigation-main-content">
</main>
  `}</code></pre>
    <p>
      This creates an empty layout to be filled with contentâ€”buttons, icons, a
      logo, a search box, and internal navigation bars structures (e.g., using
      Flexbox for layout).
    </p>
    <h2>Navbars' content and structure</h2>
    <p>
      Several utility classes are provided to help with general-purpose navbar
      layouts:
    </p>
    <p>To populate the primary sidebar you can use this template:</p>
    <pre
      data-copyable-snippet><code>{`<div class="stt-primary-sidebar-top">
  <h2>Collapsible</h2>
  <button data-stt-action="dismiss" class="stt-button">
    <svg
      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      height="40px"
      viewBox="0 -960 960 960"
      width="40px"
    >
      <path
        d="m251.33-204.67-46.66-46.66L433.33-480 204.67-708.67l46.66-46.66L480-526.67l228.67-228.66 46.66 46.66L526.67-480l228.66 228.67-46.66 46.66L480-433.33 251.33-204.67Z"
      ></path>
    </svg>
  </button>
</div>

<div>
  <hr />
    <!--Your sidebar content-->
  <hr />
</div>`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      To display items in the sidebar you can use the <code
        >clickable-item-list</code
      > class in the following structure:
    </p>
    <pre
      data-copyable-snippet><code>{`<ul class="clickable-item-list">
  <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
  <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
  <li>
    <details>
      <summary><a>Services</a></summary>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="#">Web </a>
        </li>
        <li><a href="#">Mobile Apps</a></li>
        <li>
          <details>
            <summary>Consulting</summary>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="#">Strategy</a></li>
              <li><a href="#">Marketing</a></li>
            </ul>
          </details>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </details>
  </li>
  <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
</ul>
`}</code></pre>
